text: William Patrick Fitzgerald (12 March 1874 – 25 March 1903) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood in the Victorian Football League (VFL). He died after falling from a horse in 1903. == Notes == == External links == * *Pat Fitzgerald's profile at Collingwood Forever Category:1874 births Category:1903 deaths Category:Australian rules footballers from Victoria (Australia) Category:Collingwood Football Club players
